In medium saucepan over medium-high heat, melt margarine. Add garlic; saute 1 minute. Add 1-1/3 cups water and milk; bring to a boil. Slowly stir in pasta, Special Seasonings, beans, tomato, olives and rosemary; return to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low. Gently boil uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring frequently. Stir in cheese. Serve in bowls, topped with croutons.